{"questionId":"17432","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The following diagram shows part of the graph of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2{x^2} = {\\text{si}}{{\\text{n}}^3}\\,y\">\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>si</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>n</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span> for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0 \\leqslant y \\leqslant \\pi \">\n  <mn>0</mn>\n  <mo>⩽</mo>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>⩽</mo>\n  <mi>π</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/c229d220b6ff75694fbace72de213427a66a989d.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the equation of the tangent to the curve at the point&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\frac{1}{4}{\\text{, }}\\frac{{5\\pi }}{6}} \\right)\"> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mfrac> <mn>1</mn> <mn>4</mn> </mfrac> <mrow> <mtext>,&nbsp;</mtext> </mrow> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>5</mn> <mi>π</mi> </mrow> <mn>6</mn> </mfrac> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>at&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\frac{1}{4}{\\text{, }}\\frac{{5\\pi }}{6}} \\right){\\text{, }}\\frac{{{\\text{d}}y}}{{{\\text{d}}x}} = \\frac{{4x}}{{3\\,{\\text{si}}{{\\text{n}}^2}\\,y\\,{\\text{cos}}\\,y}} = \\frac{1}{{3{{\\left( {\\frac{1}{2}} \\right)}^2}\\left( { - \\frac{{\\sqrt 3 }}{2}} \\right)}}\"> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mfrac> <mn>1</mn> <mn>4</mn> </mfrac> <mrow> <mtext>,&nbsp;</mtext> </mrow> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>5</mn> <mi>π</mi> </mrow> <mn>6</mn> </mfrac> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <mrow> <mtext>,&nbsp;</mtext> </mrow> <mfrac> <mrow> <mrow> <mtext>d</mtext> </mrow> <mi>y</mi> </mrow> <mrow> <mrow> <mtext>d</mtext> </mrow> <mi>x</mi> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>4</mn> <mi>x</mi> </mrow> <mrow> <mn>3</mn> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mrow> <mtext>si</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <msup> <mrow> <mtext>n</mtext> </mrow> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mi>y</mi> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mrow> <mtext>cos</mtext> </mrow> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mi>y</mi> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mn>1</mn> <mrow> <mn>3</mn> <mrow> <msup> <mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mfrac> <mn>1</mn> <mn>2</mn> </mfrac> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mo>−</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <msqrt> <mn>3</mn> </msqrt> </mrow> <mn>2</mn> </mfrac> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </mfrac> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\Rightarrow \\frac{{{\\text{d}}y}}{{{\\text{d}}x}} =&nbsp; - \\frac{8}{{3\\sqrt 3 }}\\left( { =&nbsp; - 1.54} \\right)\"> <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mrow> <mtext>d</mtext> </mrow> <mi>y</mi> </mrow> <mrow> <mrow> <mtext>d</mtext> </mrow> <mi>x</mi> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>=</mo> <mo>−</mo> <mfrac> <mn>8</mn> <mrow> <mn>3</mn> <msqrt> <mn>3</mn> </msqrt> </mrow> </mfrac> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mo>−</mo> <mn>1.54</mn> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>hence equation of tangent is</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y - \\frac{{5\\pi }}{6} =&nbsp; - 1.54\\left( {x - \\frac{1}{4}} \\right)\"> <mi>y</mi> <mo>−</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>5</mn> <mi>π</mi> </mrow> <mn>6</mn> </mfrac> <mo>=</mo> <mo>−</mo> <mn>1.54</mn> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mi>x</mi> <mo>−</mo> <mfrac> <mn>1</mn> <mn>4</mn> </mfrac> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span>&nbsp; <strong>OR</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y =&nbsp; - 1.54x + 3.00\"> <mi>y</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mo>−</mo> <mn>1.54</mn> <mi>x</mi> <mo>+</mo> <mn>3.00</mn> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Accept&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y =&nbsp; - 1.54x + 3\"> <mi>y</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mo>−</mo> <mn>1.54</mn> <mi>x</mi> <mo>+</mo> <mn>3</mn> </math></span>.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"17432","referenceCode":"19N.2.AHL.TZ0.H_11a.ii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the equation of the tangent to the curve at the point ( 1 4 , 5 π 6 ) .","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.4—Tangents and normal","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.14—Implicit functions, related rates, optimisation"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}